    "description": "See ticket: \r\n\r\nhttps://globusonline.zendesk.com/agent/tickets/304408\r\n\r\nUser reports that CILogonIdentityProvider option in globus-connect-server.conf for providers that contain an \"&\" character must replace the \"&\" with \"&amp;\" - e.g. \"Texas A &amp; M University\" - for the option to parse. User reports that it was possible to simply use the \"&\" character alone - e.g. \"Texas A & M University\" - in his GT 5.2 based GCS install. \r\n\r\nThis produces a gsi-authz.conf file where the DN also contains \"&amp;\" instead of \"&\". For example:\r\n\r\n# cat /var/lib/globus-connect-server/gsi-authz.conf\r\n|globus_mapping libglobus_gridmap_eppn_callout globus_gridmap_eppn_callout ENV:GLOBUS_MYPROXY_CA_CERT=/var/lib/globus-connect-server/grid-security/certificates/c2868627.0 GLOBUS_MYPROXY_AUTHORIZED_DN=\"/DC=org/DC=cilogon/C=US/O=Texas A &amp; M University\"\r\n|globus_mapping libglobus_gridmap_eppn_callout globus_gridmap_eppn_callout ENV:GLOBUS_MYPROXY_CA_CERT=/var/lib/globus-connect-server/grid-security/certificates/01b5d333.0 GLOBUS_MYPROXY_AUTHORIZED_DN=\"/DC=org/DC=cilogon/C=US/O=Texas A &amp; M University\"\r\n", 
